  "texts": [
    "Traditional polls play a useful role of cue-giving, facilitating the choice of voters in the sheer complexity of electoral democracy by providing consensus cues and possibly triggering internal deliberation.",
    "Our argument goes one step further.",
    "When it comes to making a difficult decision, it is not unreasonable to defer to someone who has more expertise or/and who shares your interest.",
    "It does not deny your autonomy to refer to the epistemic intelligence of others.",
    "If polls are remarkable cue-givers, the detail and precision of AI-driven polls brings their epistemic effect to a new level."
  ],
